od).\n*   **Finite-Lived Amortization:** Amortization expense was **$113 million** and **$206 million** for the three months ended March 31, 2026, and 2025, respectively.\n*   **Indefinite-Lived Intangibles:** Primarily consist of trade names and domain names providing long-term branding benefits. Balances were **$19 million** (Mar 31, 2026) and **$11 million** (Dec 31, 2025).\n*   **Pending Spectrum Acquisition:** The Company entered into a License Purchase Agreement with EchoStar Corporation and Spectrum Business Trust 2025-1 for AWS-3, AWS-4, and H-Block spectrum licenses (total consideration of $17 billion). Once the transfer closing occurs (expected on or about Nov 30, 2027), these licenses will be recognized as **acquired intangible assets**.\n*   **Common-Control Mergers:** No new intangible assets were recorded during the mergers of xAI and X into SpaceX.\n\n### 3. Acquisition Accounting\n*   **Common Control Reorganizations (xAI and X):** Because Elon Musk held a controlling financial interest in SpaceX, xAI, and X, the 2025/2026 mergers were accounted for as reorganizations of entities under common control, not as standard business combinations. \n    *   *Retrospective Combination:* Net assets were combined at their **historical carrying amounts** for all periods presented.\n    *   *Eliminations:* All historical related-party transactions between the entities were eliminated.\n    *   *Change in Reporting Entity:* Historical SpaceX equity was combined with X and xAI equity using the respective exchange ratios. Separate financial statements for xAI and X are not provided.\n*   **Standard Business Combinations:** For standard acquisitions, the Company records goodwill for the excess of purchase price over the fair value of identifiable net assets.\n*   **Asset Acquisitions:** Pending transactions like the EchoStar Spectrum Acquisition are treated as asset acquisitions and will be recognized as acquired intangible assets upon closing.\n*   **Potential Acquisitions (Cursor):** An option agreement exists to acquire Cursor. If exercised, a merger agreement would be executed to acquire Cursor\'s cash, IP, personnel, and customer contracts, with the purchase price primarily allocated to goodwill.\n\n### 4. xAI Purchase Price Allocation\n*   **No Traditional Purchase Price Allocation:** Because the xAI Merger (completed Feb 2, 2026) and the preceding X Merger (completed Mar 28, 2025) were accounted for as **reorganizations of entities under common control**, the Company did *not* apply standard acquisition accounting (ASC 805). \n*   **Historical Carrying Amounts:** There was no "stepping up" of assets to fair value. The net assets of xAI and X were absorbed into SpaceX\'s consolidated financial statements at their **historical carrying amounts**.\n*   **No New Goodwill or Intangibles:** As a direct result of the common-control accounting treatment, **no new goodwill or other intangible assets were recorded** for the xAI or X mergers.\n*   **Equity Consideration:** The transactions were effected through share exchanges. xAI\'s historical redeemable convertible preferred stock was not recast retrospectively; instead, its conversion into SpaceX Common Stock was recognized prospectively in the period the merger actually occurred (Q1 2026), resulting in a $37,475 million shift from Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock to Common Stock and Additional Paid-in Capital on the equity statement.',
