    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output="Based on the provided excerpts from the S-1 prospectus and financial statement notes, here are the detailed insights regarding share-based compensation, stock option valuation, fair value assumptions, and dilution:\n\n### 1. Share-Based Compensation Details\n**Expense Recognition Policies:**\n*   **Service Conditions:** Recognized on a straight-line basis over the requisite service period.\n*   **Performance Conditions:** Recognized on a graded vesting basis when the vesting of the award becomes probable. For CEO awards with market/performance conditions, expense is not recognized until the performance condition is deemed probable.\n*   **Forfeitures:** Accounted for as they occur rather than estimated upfront.\n*   **Capitalization:** Share-based compensation capitalized to the consolidated balance sheets was $154 million (2025), $132 million (2024), and $108 million (2023). No income tax benefit was recognized due to a valuation allowance on U.S. deferred tax assets.\n\n**Compensation Expense Breakdown (in millions):**\n| Line Item | 2025 | 2024 | 2023 |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| Cost of revenue | $253 | $193 | $167 |\n| Research and development | $859 | $230 | $179 |\n| Selling, general, and administrative | $835 | $360 | $333 |\n| **Total Expense** | **$1,947** | **$784** | **$679** |\n\n**Specific Executive & Employee Awards:**\n*   **Elon Musk’s xAI Award (Nov 2025):** A performance-based award consisting of 12 tranches. Each tranche grants shares equal to 1.0% of xAI’s valuation at specific milestones (ranging from $213B to $1,313B). It included a market condition, a performance condition (raising $\\ge$ $2B from investors), and a 10-year service condition. The grant date fair value was $2,205 million, with $28 million expensed in 2025. *Note: This award was terminated in March 2026.*\n*   **SpaceX & AI CEO Awards:** These awards lack a defined performance period other than continued employment. An expected term midpoint of 30 years (from a 10-50 year analysis) was used for valuation.\n*   **X Employee RSUs (March 2023):** Originally subject to a liquidity event (change in control or IPO). In 2025, the performance condition was removed, resulting in additional share-based compensation expense.\n*   **CFO Award:** Modified to include an additional one-year and one-day service-based vesting requirement following the fiscal year a tranche is earned. The impact was not material.\n\n**Merger Conversions & Plan Terms:**\n*   **xAI Merger:** xAI options, RSUs, and RSAs were converted into SpaceX equity at a **0.1433** ratio (pre-2026 Stock Split basis). Exercise prices were divided by 0.1433.\n*   **X Merger:** Outstanding X RSUs were converted to xAI RSUs at a **2.776** ratio.\n*   **A&R 2024 Plan:** Options have a max term of 10 years (5 years for 10% shareholders' ISOs). Exercise prices cannot be less than Fair Market Value (FMV) on the grant date (110% of FMV for 10% shareholders' ISOs).\n\n---\n\n### 2. Stock Option & Equity Award Valuation\n**Valuation Methodologies:**\n*   **Employee Stock Options:** Valued using the **Black-Scholes option-pricing model**.\n*   **CEO Awards (xAI, SpaceX, AI):** Valued using a **Monte Carlo simulation model** due to complex market, service, and performance conditions.\n*   **RSUs, RSAs, and ESPP:** Valued based on the fair market value of the Company’s common stock on the grant/offering date.\n\n**Fair Value & Intrinsic Value Metrics:**\n*   **Stock Options:** Weighted-average grant-date fair value per share was $21.29 (2025), $5.02 (2024), and $7.60 (2023). Total intrinsic value of options exercised was $1,249M (2025), $392M (2024), and $261M (2023).\n*   **RSUs:** Weighted-average grant-date fair value per share was $54.84 (2025), $17.68 (2024), and $15.60 (2023). Total fair market value of RSUs released was $2,151M (2025), $871M (2024), and $729M (2023).\n*   **RSAs:** Weighted-average grant-date fair value was $93.87 (2025), $0.00 (2024/2023).\n*   **Unrecognized Expense:** As of Dec 31, 2025, total remaining share-based compensation expense for unvested options, RSUs, and RSAs was **$4,842 million**, expected to be recognized over a weighted-average period of **3.2 years**.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Fair Value Assumptions\n**Employee Stock Options (Black-Scholes):**\n| Assumption | 2025 | 2024 | 2023 | Methodology |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Expected term (years)** | 6.94 | 6.80 | 6.70 | Simplified method (mid-point between vesting and contractual life). |\n| **Volatility** | 43.14% | 39.80% | 43.20% | Daily historical prices of comparable public companies. |\n| **Risk-free interest rate** | 4.02% | 4.30% | 3.60% | U.S. Government securities matching the expected term. |\n| **Dividend yield** | 0.00% | 0.00% | 0.00% | Company has never paid and does not anticipate paying dividends. |\n\n**CEO & Executive Awards (Monte Carlo Simulation):**\n| Assumption | CEO xAI Award | SpaceX & AI CEO Awards |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Expected term (years)** | 10.0 | 30.0 (Midpoint of 10-50 year analysis due to undefined performance periods) |\n| **Volatility** | 45% – 55% | 45.0% |\n| **Risk-free interest rate** | 4.06% | 4.91% |\n| **Dividend yield** | 0.00% | 0.00% |\n\n---\n\n### 4. Dilution & Earnings Per Share (EPS)\n**EPS Methodology & Deemed Dividends:**\n*   **Two-Class Method:** Used for participating securities. Certain redeemable convertible preferred stocks participate in dividends on an as-converted basis but *do not* participate in net losses.\n*   **Deemed Dividends:** The excess of fair market value over the consideration transferred for repurchasing SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock was treated as a deemed dividend. This decreased net income (or increased net loss) attributable to common shareholders.\n\n**Anti-Dilutive Securities Excluded from Diluted EPS:**\nPotentially dilutive securities were excluded from the diluted EPS calculation because their impact would be anti-dilutive. \n\n*Excluded Securities (in millions, as of December 31):*\n| Security Type | 2025 | 2024 | 2023 |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock | 1,369 | — | 537 |\n| SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock | 6,733 | — | 6,780 |\n| Share-based compensation | 623 | 18 | 767 |\n*Note: Additionally, 14.5M (2025), 38.3M (2024), and 21.2M (2023) SBC awards were excluded because performance/market conditions were not met.*\n\n*Excluded Securities (in millions, as of March 31 - Q1):*\n| Security Type | 2026 | 2025 |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock | — | 1,155 |\n| SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock | 6,723 | 6,760 |\n| Share-based compensation | 598 | 674 |\n*Note: Additionally, 1,319.1M (2026) and 14.3M (2025) SBC awards were excluded as performance/market conditions were not met.*",
